## What this means in practice

### Permitted — without restriction

- Using FreeckFonts daily as a tool in your professional or commercial
  workflow (design, video editing, copywriting, development, etc.)
- Installing, managing, and browsing fonts for any project, commercial
  or otherwise
- Modifying the source code for your own use
- Contributing to the project
- Redistributing the software free of charge with this license intact
- Using the software in educational institutions, non-profits,
  government agencies, or any organization

### Not permitted — requires written authorization

- Selling FreeckFonts or a derivative as a standalone product
- Offering FreeckFonts functionality as a paid hosted service (SaaS)
- Bundling the source code or compiled binary into a commercial product
  or service whose value derives substantially from FreeckFonts
- Charging fees for access to, distribution of, or support contracts
  centered on the Software itself

For commercial licensing inquiries, contact the project maintainers.

